In terms of story it was all right, but it was a pretty basic plot. I'm sure everyone here has seen the plot, backstory, corruption/whatever happens, reformation, corruption/whatever again, ending without much gratification. It's a usual plot that's been used before and will continue to be used again. What they did with this basic premise was good, but I just feel as if it could have been fleshed out a bit more.

About the art: the art itself was actually very good, it had very clean lines without any overly-exaggerated body parts as we see in a lot of hentai within the same genre, ntr, and some very detailed shots. They missed out on a few really good opportunities for page-spreads, but overall it was great.

About any extras, I feel as if the pacing was a bit off, changed a lot. You could notice that a few scenes moved fast in places where a slower moment would have better suited it and vice versa, but that's about it.

Final rating? 7/10, not my best, certainly not my worst.
